The paper deals with deep neural networks and their interpretability in classification tasks, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of variational autoencoders and Kullback-Leibler divergence also suggests a focus on generative models and probabilistic inference, which are common in these sub-fields.
